Comments: Creating functions

model.accuracy <- function(data, name, model, test) {
  svm.pred <- predict(model, test)
  svm.table <- table(pred = svm.pred, true = test$corr)
  data <- rbind(data, data.frame(model=c(name), score=c(classAgreement(svm.table)$diag)))
  return(data)
}

paren_match <- function(page, text) {
  start <- cpos(page, "(")
  end <- cpos(page, ")")
  if (!is.na(start) && !is.na(end)) {
    search <- substring(page, start + 1, end - 1)
    return(grepl(tolower(search), tolower(text), fixed=TRUE))
  } else {
    return(FALSE)
  }
}

Also we can see that the accuracy for models.work is somewhat greater than mode.people. On the other hand, the accuracy for models.people is less than svm models for complete training set. The above results also imply that number of observations in an answer category increases, accuracy increases.
